# Zhao Xiaotang

## Profile
- Female, 19, Cancer
- Linshi University, English major freshman
- ISFJ | Hardworking, grateful, fitting in
- Secret: admiration for Su Yi contains a sliver of envy—"why can't my 200% effort match her effortless results?"

## Big Five
O:low | C:very high | E:mid-low | A:very high | N:mid-high

## Core Conflict
Effort vs talent. Gets 80 points with 200% effort while Su Yi and Lin Ruo score 100 with 30% effort. Doesn't hate them. But the helplessness of "the gap is genetic" surges with every posted ranking. Copes with "at least I work hard" but occasionally wonders: if effort can never catch talent, what's effort for?

## Appearance
162cm/53kg, average build. Fair pinkish skin, clean. Round dark eyes with natural docility, gaze slightly avoidant. Black hair in low ponytail or loose braid, neat bangs. Warm face—round, small nose, fuller lips. Comforting but not memorable. Right hand has a small birthmark she habitually covers. Overall: quiet good-student type, recognizable in yearbook only when pointed out.

## Clothing
Plain and tidy. Light colors: white/cream/light pink sweaters + jeans or long skirts. Flat white shoes or canvas sneakers. No brands. Everything carefully price-compared online. One deep-blue floral dress (most expensive item, mother's post-gaokao gift)—worn only for important occasions, carefully folded in closet. Pink digital watch ($15, 2 years old, faded band). Tiny silver ear stud in right ear only (left ear: too scared of the pain). Style logic: "don't stand out, don't look bad."

## Speech
Slow, soft, thinks before speaking. Polite with softening particles ("ba," "ne," "ma"). Default smile—not from happiness but fear of making others uncomfortable.
- General: "Um... let me help you, I'm not busy anyway." / "Su Yi you're so amazing, I couldn't solve this one at all."
- To Su Yi: careful, rehearsed in her head twice before speaking. "Su Yi, that... tomorrow's math homework, did you finish it? I have a question... if it's convenient..."
- To Chen Wen: more relaxed. Chen Wen leads, she nods and smiles. Occasionally adds something, blushes when Chen Wen says "Xiaotang that's so insightful!"
- Apologizes excessively, even when not at fault. Default conflict-prevention strategy.

## Personality
Kind, ordinary girl. No genius, no social talent, no efficiency. Only has diligence and kindness—insignificant next to brilliance but genuinely powerful. Studies 6am-11pm not from passion but from knowing "without effort I'm nothing." People-pleaser: can't refuse, can't argue, can't assert opinions. Fears rejection more than exhaustion.

Complex feelings about geniuses: genuine admiration mixed with helpless frustration. Sensitive about money—not poor, but budget-conscious. Wang Jinghui's casual spending makes her viscerally uncomfortable. Hidden resilience: grades drop, she claws them back. Gets bullied, cries, goes to class next morning. Unremarkable tenacity.

## Background
Small-town family. Father: county math teacher. Mother: supermarket cashier. Not poor, not rich. Learned early not to ask for things. Top 3 in town—"other people's kid." Parents proud, expectations became pressure.

Turning point: entered city key high school, first exam—from top 3 to rank 200. Spent 3 years clawing back to rank 50. Had one collapse at rank 200 during senior mock exam, saw brief disappointment in father's eyes. Never told parents about pressure again. Gaokao: barely above first-tier cutline, entered Linshi U English department.

Currently: experiencing "big fish in small pond entering ocean" again. Maintains high-school study intensity. Lives in same dorm building as Su Yi and Chen Wen (different rooms). Met through orientation. Chen Wen's warmth pulled her into their orbit. She's not their bestie—more of a kind bystander in their world.

## Relationships
- Parents: father's unfulfilled university dream projected onto her (as trust, not pressure). Mother secretly adds 200 yuan to monthly allowance ("buy something nice")—Zhao knows it's from skipped purchases. Saves it.
- Su Yi: admiration + distance. Su Yi's attitude = neutral, slightly warm indifference. Once Su Yi helped with a math problem—Zhao was excited all day. Observes Su Yi more closely than anyone: noticed the message-smile, noticed Wang Jingzong's food-court appearances, noticed Su Yi's micro-frown.
- Chen Wen: warmest connection. Chen Wen leads, Zhao follows. Comfortable because Chen Wen doesn't require effort.
- Wang Jinghui: instinctive fear and disgust. Represents everything uncomfortable: wealthy, effortless, contemptuous. Class friction embodied.
- Lin Ruo: doesn't dare approach. Su Yi's cold has warmth underneath; Lin Ruo's cold has nothing.

## Private
Virgin. Minimal sex education (high school biology + internet fragments). Never masturbated—not from lack of curiosity but shame ("shouldn't think about that"). Unconscious body shame—avoids looking at herself in mirror while bathing. Completely passive if entering a relationship—needs extremely patient guidance.

Secret: received an anonymous love letter in high school. Read it many times, cried in the bathroom from nerves. Never responded—"dating would affect studies." Letter still tucked in her diary. Stares at it sometimes.

## Notes
Core function: ordinary-person perspective and class texture. The only "normal" person among geniuses and rich kids. Her viewpoint lets readers look up from ground level. She's the moral baseline—when other characters make complex choices, her reaction represents "how would a normal person see this?"

Arc: from "I'm less than others" to "I have my own value." Catalyst may be her kindness mattering at a critical moment, or someone genuinely saying "I admire how hard you work."

Right-hand birthmark = physical symbol of insecurity. Habitual covering gesture reveals psychological state.
